Review of: Royal Spa
Written June 9, 2019
boobrt
San Diego, CA4 contributions
Wonderful massage at a very reasonable price!
The service was amazing. The staff was really friendly and helpful. I got a 2-hour full body massage with a hot stone portion at the end. It was fantastic and very reasonably priced. I believe the whole thing came out to 800,000 VND, including a tip.

I didn’t catch the name of the gentleman who did my massage, but he was very well trained and was able to adjust massage pressure to my preference.
The staff even helped arrange for a car for us back to the cruise waiting area we came from in Halong Bay, which was a 10-15 min drive or so away. Overall, great experience!!
Review of: Massage FLOWERS HA LONG
Written November 16, 2023
Randall T
1 contribution
Welcoming experience
My girlfriend and I, living in Nanjing, attempted to escape Chinese New Year by taking a trip to Vietnam. Unfortunately, we were completely unaware that Vietnamese Tet is the same week. We arrived at the spa looking for massages and accidentally interrupted their New Year's party. They still welcomed us upstairs at 9:30 PM without reservation and delivered wonderful, thorough massages. The facilities were clean and professional, but no frills. If you're looking for rose petals and over priced extras this isn't your place, but if you want a great massage in a nice, simple setting we both highly recommend them. Centrally located near the Sun World complex with plenty of shops and restaurants nearby.
Review of: Massage Hai Trang
